What we learn as we let runs go on for longer is that eventually , the dispersion of losses for the validators becomes larger. 

This is bad because :

- We need to improve VTrust . We can only do this if the model states between the validators are in sync. 

I just mentioned it to @Daniel [τ, τ] and he knew why  (or at least provided a credible explanation of why).

- Miners always sync with the high staked validator. 
- Over time , the miners sync more with V1 then the rest of the validators , as they restart and pull its state. 

Not sure what the best way to solve this is, but a Daniel team cut our work in half. TY!
